with the Apaches?

12:12.680 --> 12:15.001
- Has she told her father yet?
- No.

12:15.080 --> 12:16.730
He'll fucking shoot you, man.

12:16.800 --> 12:18.165
ARTHUR: Are you sure the kid is yours?

12:18.240 --> 12:19.890
MICHAEL: (SIGHS)
I wish I hadn't told you.

12:20.000 --> 12:23.209
Then think of marriage
as a beautiful road...

12:23.400 --> 12:25.402
Flowers all the way down it.

12:25.480 --> 12:27.926
- Is he joking?
- It's hard to tell these days.

12:31.400 --> 12:32.845
Do you, er...

12:33.760 --> 12:35.091
Do you love the woman?

12:37.360 --> 12:38.566
Fucking what?

12:38.680 --> 12:40.330
Well, then go and marry her
like the rest of us.

12:40.440 --> 12:42.841
She doesn't want her family to know.

12:43.040 --> 12:44.485
And she doesn't want to have the baby.

12:44.560 --> 12:45.561
We know a woman.

12:45.680 --> 12:48.251
- Shut up, john.
- Same woman who helped you out, twice.

12:48.360 --> 12:49.885
- They weren't my women.
- Mmm-hmm.

12:50.360 --> 12:51.964
That's why you had them fixed, Arthur.

12:52.400 --> 12:53.686
Charlotte will want the best...

12:53.880 --> 12:55.405
-jOHN: She is the best.
-"The best."

12:55.480 --> 12:58.086
JOHN: Used to be a nurse.
Twenty minutes. Done.

12:58.160 --> 13:00.731
And you don't have to go to in
or wait outside.

13:01.120 --> 13:02.326
You go to the Garrison.

13:02.600 --> 13:04.364
Drink whisky. Have a laugh.

13:04.960 --> 13:06.166
Remember, john?

13:07.000 --> 13:10.846
And then this kid walks in, no shoes on,
says, "it's done".

13:11.440 --> 13:12.885
Second time we was in there.

13:13.080 --> 13:17.961
Same kid, this time he is wearing
shiny new shoes.

13:19.760 --> 13:22.889
- And he shouts, "It's done, Arthur."
- And what?

13:26.320 --> 13:27.970
She bought new shoes

13:30.200 --> 13:31.611
with the money I gave her.

13:33.640 --> 13:34.971
It was for a good cause.

13:35.560 --> 13:36.561
Arthur?

13:36.840 --> 13:38.968
If you are going to get on
like this with the Apaches,

13:39.040 --> 13:40.405
they'd fucking scalp you, boy.

13:40.640 --> 13:42.005
(BELL RINGS)

13:43.160 --> 13:46.369
Tommy said when that bell rings
we've to all go to the big room.

13:52.360 --> 13:54.840
Come on.
Tommy has a plan.

14:12.000 --> 14:13.001
Arthur.

14:13.920 --> 14:15.570
- Arthur.
- TOMMY: Arthur, come here.

14:17.280 --> 14:19.362
- ALFIE: Shalom.
-(ARTHUR GRUNTS)

14:20.080 --> 14:22.367
ALFIE: Arthur, shalom.

14:23.000 --> 14:25.002
- Alfie.
- Shalom...

14:25.360 --> 14:26.885
Come here. Come on. Listen...

14:26.960 --> 14:29.042
I owe you a little something, don't I?

14:29.120 --> 14:30.724
I do. Come on.

14:30.960 --> 14:32.121
Sit down.

14:32.800 --> 14:34.131
Come on, sit down here.

14:34.440 --> 14:35.601
There you go.

14:36.680 --> 14:37.681
Right.

14:39.000 --> 14:40.001
Listen.

14:40.840 --> 14:41.841
Arthur.

14:42.920 --> 14:44.524
I want you to know, right,

14:44.840 --> 14:48.083
that whatever happened
between us, yeah? Back then...

14:48.480 --> 14:50.448
- That was business.
-(BREATHING DEEPLY)

14:50.760 --> 14:52.649
It was just business.
All right?

14:53.760 --> 14:55.728
And I also want you to know

14:56.280 --> 14:58.282
that I have made my apologies

14:58.920 --> 15:03.687
via my own God
for abusing a very holy day

15:03.920 --> 15:07.208
to get you clinked up and battered,
which I did.

15:08.000 --> 15:13.689
And, now, I would also like to extend
my personal apologies unto you.

15:23.120 --> 15:24.201
All right?

15:26.800 --> 15:30.282
I hear that you have allowed Jesus
to come into your life.

15:30.480 --> 15:31.481
Eh...

15:32.080 --> 15:33.411
Oh, you heard then.

15:33.480 --> 15:35.369
Yeah. That is beautiful.
That is wonderful.

15:35.440 --> 15:36.771
That is lovely, isn't it?

15:37.000 --> 15:38.126
That is lovely.

15:39.120 --> 15:41.885
But I was wondering,
how does that work for you

15:41.960 --> 15:44.566
on a day-to-day considering
your line of work, mate?

15:49.560 --> 15:51.085
Your apology's accepted.

15:54.120 --> 15:56.600
'Cause I hear
you're a right fucking nuisance with it.

15:57.120 --> 15:58.121
(scoffs)

15:59.880 --> 16:01.450
Hello...

16:02.240 --> 16:06.450
Listen, all I am saying is that,
every man, he craves certainty.

16:06.520 --> 16:12.368
He craves the certainty, even if
that certainty of yours, right...

16:12.480 --> 16:13.970
Well, I mean...

16:14.960 --> 16:17.691
It's fucking fanciful mate, innit?

16:17.760 --> 16:19.364
(RAGGED BREATHING)

16:19.560 --> 16:20.925
ALFIE: Eh?

16:32.920 --> 16:36.561
I'm Old Testament.

16:38.480 --> 16:40.847
Fucking hell. Look at that. Now, that...

16:42.560 --> 16:44.608
That scares me more...

16:45.360 --> 16:46.361
Yeah.

16:46.920 --> 16:48.524
Congratulations, Tommy.

16:48.600 --> 16:51.683
You now have the finished article
right here, don't you?

16:51.960 --> 16:57.569
See, that man, right? He will murder
and maim for you with God on his side.

16:58.960 --> 17:00.325
Yeah.

17:03.480 --> 17:05.448
You don't want to let him go.

17:06.839 --> 17:09.810
ARTHUR: If we're gonna do business
with this fucker,

17:09.880 --> 17:11.608
I demand to know why.

17:15.960 --> 17:17.450
TOMMY: Right...

17:18.000 --> 17:19.729
While I was in the hospital,

17:20.599 --> 17:22.329
I formulated a plan.

17:25.480 --> 17:27.130
And this is how it is going to work.

17:28.040 --> 17:30.486
So the Russians cannot be trusted
to pay us.

17:31.880 --> 17:34.087
We are going to take what is ours.

17:35.240 --> 17:37.129
We need to see
what's in their treasury.

17:38.840 --> 17:41.571
And that is why we need Mr Solomons.

18:03.200 --> 18:09.242
(SIGHING) Right, boys,just remember
they are fucking insane...

18:09.720 --> 18:11.404
And dangerous...

18:11.560 --> 18:13.642
And drunk on stuff we've never heard of.

18:14.440 --> 18:17.125
And they're worse than us
for spirits and ghosts.

18:20.360 --> 18:23.284
And, today, they're going to test us.

18:25.040 --> 18:26.246
Fuck them.

18:33.840 --> 18:36.810
ARTHUR: The Russians
all turned and ran.

18:37.680 --> 18:39.682
The Cossacks didn't run, Arthur.

18:52.320 --> 18:54.402
Mr Shelby. Welcome.

18:54.760 --> 18:55.807
How is my car?

18:55.960 --> 18:57.564
I think I am in love with it.

18:57.760 --> 18:59.205
And I yours.

18:59.760 --> 19:01.728
So we should keep what we love, yes?

19:01.960 --> 19:03.041
Excuse the reception,

19:03.120 --> 19:05.805
whenever we open the treasury,
the Cossacks are on guard...

19:11.560 --> 19:12.561
(s PITS)

19:14.680 --> 19:17.763
<i>TOMMY". In Russia,
men on the other side of the law</i>

19:18.120 --> 19:20.202
<i>decorate their body in tattoos.</i>

19:20.360 --> 19:21.521
-jOHN: Nice.
- Right...

19:21.760 --> 19:24.923
Now, some of these tattoos
are proof of allegiance

19:25.560 --> 19:27.289
to underground organisations,

19:27.760 --> 19:30.525
which are the sworn enemies
of the royal household.

19:30.600 --> 19:36.846
So it is customary
in Russian royal households

19:37.160 --> 19:40.289
to check for such tattoos
before engaging a man in business.

19:40.920 --> 19:42.763
And as we approach the allotted day

19:42.840 --> 19:44.490
these ladies here
would like to make sure

19:44.560 --> 19:47.564
that you are
not assassins or infiltrators, so...

19:47.640 --> 19:48.766
No, we're all good.

19:48.840 --> 19:50.444
So they'd like to check your skin.

19:52.680 --> 19:54.444
They want to check our skin?

19:55.040 --> 19:56.041
Yeah.

19:56.120 --> 19:57.724
Now my body has already been checked,

19:57.800 --> 20:00.770
although, at the time,
I wasn't sure that was the reason.

20:01.480 --> 20:02.811
And now it's your turn.

20:04.120 --> 20:05.360
Well then, boys.

20:05.800 --> 20:07.370
Take your clothes off.

20:07.880 --> 20:08.881
(scoffs)

20:09.000 --> 20:10.126
Fuck off.

20:10.440 --> 20:12.522
No. No. No. No. No...

20:12.600 --> 20:13.761
IZABELLA: Obey.

20:15.600 --> 20:17.011
Obey, Arthur. (CHUCKLES)

20:18.520 --> 20:21.444
No, I won't be obeying nobody.
Get out of my way.

20:21.520 --> 20:22.726
Arthur. Come here...

20:25.440 --> 20:29.490
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

20:36.040 --> 20:37.041
Eh?

20:41.120 --> 20:42.929
JOHN: (CHUCKLING)
Come on, Arthur.

20:43.360 --> 20:44.407
ARTHUR: Shut up,john.

20:44.480 --> 20:45.641
(JOHN LAUGHING)

20:45.960 --> 20:50.522
(LAUGHS) I will have a maid
gather the buttons and sew them back on.

20:51.120 --> 20:52.121
(JOHN SCOFFS)

20:53.000 --> 20:54.490
(SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN)

20:54.920 --> 20:55.967
Hmm.

21:06.160 --> 21:09.289
All right. Fuck it.

21:09.440 --> 21:10.930
There you go, ladies.

21:11.200 --> 21:14.010
- Made in fucking Birmingham.
-(j0HN LAUGHS)

21:15.640 --> 21:18.007
All right, I think
we've seen enough, eh?

21:19.680 --> 21:20.806
IZABELLA: Tatiana.

21:24.560 --> 21:26.050
(JOHN STIFLES LAUGH)

21:26.160 --> 21:28.891
Your face, Arthur, is a fucking picture.

21:29.040 --> 21:32.522
Sometimes assassins hide
their allegiances behind their balls.

21:32.600 --> 21:33.601
(GAS PS SO FTLY)

21:39.400 --> 21:41.164
You pass the test, soldier.

21:42.880 --> 21:44.291
With flying colours.

21:50.040 --> 21:51.041
(JOHN LAUGHS)

21:51.320 --> 21:52.321
(GAS PS)

21:56.400 --> 21:57.731
You see?

22:00.400 --> 22:02.289
He wants to be a good man.

22:03.680 --> 22:06.001
<i>(ARTHUR BREATHXNG HEAVXLY)</i>

